oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: photograph of Pvt. Frank M. Ring, Co. A, 114th MG Battn., 30th Div.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: A portrait format photograph of a young man in the uniform of the United States Army circa 1918. He is wearing a campaign hat with cords and uniform coat with standing collar. There are no insignia visible on the sleeves and the collar is without devices. Hand written on the reverse in pencil "Frank M. Ring." Frank Ring was killed in action in October 1918 and bureid in France. His two older brothers also served in World War I. They both survived the war.
